                <h1>Understanding CSI: The Essential Guide to Crime Scene Investigation</h1>
                <p>CSI, or Crime Scene Investigation, refers to the process of collecting and analyzing evidence from a crime scene to solve criminal cases. This multidisciplinary field involves forensic science, law enforcement techniques, and meticulous attention to detail to reconstruct events and identify suspects, making it vital for justice.</p>
